Below is a worked‐through example of how one can match and assemble the target “rocket” structure using the provided block dictionary.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Total Block Count: 7 blocks  
• Layering:
  – Bottom Layer (3 blocks):  
    1.  A central arch.  
    2.  Left and right wedges, each sloping upward toward the center.  
  – Middle Layer (2 blocks):  
    3.  One green cube on the left.  
    4.  One blue cube on the right.  
  – Top Layer (2 blocks):  
    5.  Two wedge blocks meeting in the middle to form a “pitched‐roof” peak.

• Spatial Relationships:
  – The arch sits in the bottom center, with one wedge on each side making a wide base.  
  – Above the arch and wedges, two cubes (green left, blue right) form the middle band.  
  – Finally, two triangular wedges rest on top, meeting at a center ridge and creating the rocket‐like roof.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below are the dictionary indices that match each needed piece exactly in shape, color, **and** orientation (no rotations allowed other than how they appear in the dictionary):

• Bottom Layer  
  – Center Arch: Block #1  
  – Left Wedge:  Block #14  
  – Right Wedge: Block #16  

• Middle Layer  
  – Green Cube:  Block #6  
  – Blue Cube:   Block #5  

• Top Layer  
  – Left “Roof” Wedge:  Block #14 (used again)  
  – Right “Roof” Wedge: Block #16 (used again)  

Thus you will need:  
{1, 5, 6, 14, 14, 16, 16}

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP-BY-STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is an example build sequence.  Simply follow these moves in order:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 14   // bottom left wedge
  Step2:  Move block with index 1    // arch in center
  Step3:  Move block with index 16   // bottom right wedge
  Step4:  Move block with index 6    // green cube above arch (left side)
  Step5:  Move block with index 5    // blue cube above arch (right side)
  Step6:  Move block with index 14   // top left wedge (roof)
  Step7:  Move block with index 16   // top right wedge (roof)
}

That completes the rocket‐shaped structure exactly as shown in the target image.
